#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:39
msgid "The Browser panel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:15
msgid ""
"The QGIS Browser panel is a great tool for browsing, searching, "
"inspecting, copying and loading QGIS resources. Only resources that QGIS "
"knows how to handle are shown in the browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:20
msgid ""
"Using the Browser panel you can locate, inspect and add data, as "
"described in :ref:`browser_panel`. In addition, the Browser panel "
"supports drag and drop of many QGIS resources, such as project files, "
"Python scripts, Processing scripts and Processing models."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:26
msgid ""
"Python scripts, Processing scripts and Processing models can also be "
"opened for editing in an external editor and the graphical modeller."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:29
msgid ""
"You can drag and drop layers from the :guilabel:`Layers` panel to the "
":guilabel:`Browser` panel, for instance into a GeoPackage or a PostgreSQL"
" database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:41
msgid ""
"The browser panel (:numref:`figure_browser_panel`) is organised as an "
"expandable hierarchy with some fixed top-level entries that organise the "
"resources handled by the browser. Node entries are expanded by clicking "
"on |browserExpand| to the left of the entry name. A branch is collapsed "
"by clicking on |browserCollapse|. The |collapseTree| :sup:`Collapse All` "
"button collapses all top-level entries."
msgstr ""

