#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:405
msgid "Importing vector layers into databases using Browser panel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:407
msgid ""
"QGIS allows you to import vector layers directly into a database from the"
" :guilabel:`Browser` panel. This provides a simple way to transfer "
"datasets into supported database formats without using |dbManager| "
":sup:`DB Manager` (see :ref:`dbmanager`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:644
msgid "dbManager"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:411
msgid "You can start the import in two ways:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:413
msgid ""
"Drag and drop a single vector layer from the Browser panel or from the "
"Project into a database connection or schema item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:415
msgid ""
"Right-click on a database connection or schema item and choose "
":guilabel:`Import Vector Layer...` from the context menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:418
msgid ""
"When multiple layers are dragged into a database, they are imported "
"immediately without further options. All imports run in the background, "
"so the QGIS interface remains responsive during the process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:427
msgid "Import Vector Layer dialog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:429
msgid ""
"To add a layer using :guilabel:`Import Vector Layer...` follow these "
"steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:431
msgid ""
"Add :guilabel:`Source layer`: the layer to import, chosen from the "
"current QGIS project. To import only selected features of the source "
"layer use the |checkbox| :guilabel:`Selected features only` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:433
msgid ""
"Set the :guilabel:`Table name`: the name of the destination table in the "
"database. By default, it is taken from the source layer name but can be "
"modified. You can also use the |checkbox| :guilabel:`Replace destination "
"table (if exists)` to overwrite an existing table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:437
msgid ""
"Define the :guilabel:`Output CRS`: the coordinate reference system of the"
" destination table. By default, it is the CRS of the source layer, but it"
" can be changed using the :ref:`CRS selector <crs_selector>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:440
msgid "Configure the :guilabel:`Attributes`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:442
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Source expression`: expression used to populate the field. By "
"default, this corresponds to the original source field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:444
msgid ":guilabel:`Name`: name of the field in the destination table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:445
msgid ":guilabel:`Type`: field data type (integer, text, real, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:446
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Length` and :guilabel:`Precision`: length and precision of the"
" field, where applicable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:448
msgid ""
":guilabel:`Constraints`: rules to enforce on the field values (e.g. NOT "
"NULL, UNIQUE, DEFAULT). Support depends on the destination database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:450
msgid ":guilabel:`Alias`: an alternate display name for the field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:451
msgid ":guilabel:`Comment`: a description or note attached to the field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:453
msgid "You can use buttons on the right side to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:455
msgid ""
"|newAttribute| :sup:`Add new field` to add a new field to the destination"
" table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:658
msgid "newAttribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:456
msgid ""
"|deleteAttribute| :sup:`Delete selected field` to remove a field from the"
" destination table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:646
msgid "deleteAttribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:457
msgid ""
"|arrowUp| :sup:`Move selected field up` or |arrowDown| :sup:`Move "
"selected field down` to reorder fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:630
msgid "arrowUp"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:628
msgid "arrowDown"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:458
msgid ""
"|clearText| :sup:`Reset all fields` to clear all fields and start from "
"scratch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:638
msgid "clearText"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:459
msgid ""
"|settings| :sup:`Convert All Fields To Lowercase` or |settings| "
":sup:`Convert All Fields To Uppercase`, to change the case of all field "
"names."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:668
msgid "settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:462
msgid ""
"Optionally, apply a spatial filter with :ref:`Filter by Extent "
"<extent_selector>`. This restricts the import to features within a "
"defined bounding box."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/introduction/browser.rst:465
msgid ""
"Optionally, apply an attribute filter with :ref:`Feature filter "
"<expression_builder>`. This allows you to use an expression to select "
"which features are imported."
msgstr ""

